{{italic title}}
'''''Azem, ti je gjallë''''' ({{lang-en|Azem, you are alive}}) is a 2008 [[documentary film]] about the Albanian political leader [[Azem Hajdari]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keshilliministrave.al/?fq%3Dbrenda%26m%3Dnews%26lid%3D9225%26gj%3Dgj1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-04-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928184355/http://www.keshilliministrave.al/?fq=brenda&m=news&lid=9225&gj=gj1 |archivedate=2011-09-28 |df= }}</ref> directed by [[Saimir Kumbaro]].<ref>http://lajme.shqiperia.com/lajme/artikull/iden/77462/titulli/Azem-ti-je-gjalle-nje-film-per-heroin</ref>

==Azem Hajdari==
'''[[Azem Hajdari]]''' (March 11, 1963 - September 12, 1998), was the leader of the student's movement in 1990-1991 which overthrew communism in Albania and then an [[Albania]]n politician of the Democratic Party. He was [[assassination|assassinated]] in [[Tirana]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/keyword/azem-hajdari ''New York Times'' about Azem Hajdari]</ref><ref>[http://dissidentvoice.org/2008/07/who-killed-azem-hajdari/ Who Killed Azem Hajdari]</ref>

